The paper deals with the problem of support recovery in compressed sensing, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses the Hammersley-Chapman-Robbins (HCR) bound, which is a statistical tool commonly used in the sub-category of mathematical statistics (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of uniform Gaussian measurement matrices, which is a topic related to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
